   476	## Lessons-learned hooks (preview for /codify after impl review)
   477	
   478	- The "stop after up" pattern doesn't work against tight-loop drainers;
   479	  the right shape is staged-up where the competing service is added
   480	  *after* the test claims its targets. Worth codifying if it survives
   481	  impl review.
   482	- `!= 137` is more robust than `== 0` for SIGKILL guards because
   483	  external images don't always install graceful handlers; codify if it
   484	  survives codex-review on the impl.
   485	- Plan-task IDs are zero-padded 4-digit (`plan-0001`), not bare-int —
   486	  doc-rot risk if not codified somewhere search-able.
   487	
   488	## Out of scope (explicit)
   489	
   490	- Branch-protection update for `compose-e2e` (deferred follow-up).
   491	- Three-role UI walkthrough (planner only; implementer + evaluator
   492	  rely on chunk-9c / 9d real-subprocess pytest coverage).
   493	- Subprocess-mode UI walkthrough (compose-smoke-subprocess covers
   494	  the subprocess loop; UI flows are mode-agnostic).
